The new wave of selling üåä | Groundswell Big news! We ve raised money to empower sales teams at Big news! We ve raised money to empower sales teams at Learn more ‚Üí Groundswell Blog üìö We re Hiring! üéâ The new wave of selling üåä by Brendan Short Tuesday, October , We ve raised our first round of funding to empower sales teams at üåä Most companies make a fundraising announcement in hopes to create a spike in website traffic, gain some followers on social, and ideally get a bunch of new It‚Äôs free marketing, great branding for future hires and investors, and hey, it‚Äôs a nice thing to send home to Mom, who still doesn‚Äôt really understand what ‚ÄúSaaS Startup‚Äù means, no matter how many ‚ÄúHow I Built This‚Äù episodes she listens to (sorry , love you!). The problem with this trend (IMHO) is that it can feel a bit Many companies say that they are here to serve the But a fundraising announcement doesn‚Äôt always read in a way that is adding value to the I believe this is So, I m going to try something different with this My goal with the next words is to humbly pass along some learnings from the + calls my and I have had over the last few months, in hopes to share helpful information that you can take action on If you re on the frontlines trying to figure out how to build the sales motion at your company , you can skip to the next section, where I hope there is a bit of information that s helpful to you and your And I d love to hear from you: what are you learning that s working? I f you want to read about our fundraise, check out the four bullet points below (likely just other investors üëÄ and our competitors üëã) ‚Äî Our round came together very quickly, as we began on Groundswell in August, started the fundraise in September, and were fully closed within Village Global led the Erik Torenberg started On Deck , and that s where Nick, Hari and I So it was fitting when they showed interest in investing via his fund, Village We had incredible conversations with amazing investors, but this was a fit for the lead investor for our first round of Raaid Hossain, my former boss, also participated through his fund, . GTMfund also gave us their vote of confidence in our And we were also able to bring on board some incredible angel investors who are GTM leaders from leading SaaS companies such as Slack, Docusign, Typeform, Snowflake, Zendesk, Workato, and many We ll use the funds to make our first hires, bring the initial product to market, and validate the hypothesis we ve come to have deep conviction If you know an incredible engineer, we d love to talk with them ‚Äî more on that towards the end of this Alright, l et‚Äôs dive Try before you buy is here to Freemium, PLG, , There is a lot of content on this topic ( here , here , and here ) ‚Äî they do a great job explaining and quantifying the importance of this new GTM We aren‚Äôt going to spend any time convincing you it‚Äôs the right move for your Instead, we want to share our learnings in talking with + folks on the front lines, who already have successfully implemented a sales motion, and are actively improving it Buyers are using products before ever engaging with sales I observed this last year, while I was working at The problem is, the tools for sellers have not kept up to meet buyers where they re at, in their new way of buying . We believe that the future wave of selling is consultative and adds value in every We don‚Äôt want cold emails to random We want to help facilitate more efficient interactions between buyers and This world is better for both buyers and Below are the top four lessons we‚Äôve learned so far in talking with the top leaders at companies who are navigating the complexities of having both a (PLG) and (Enterprise sales) Learning #1 - Key Stakeholders Who should own this project at your company? Operationalizing a motion for your revenue team requires many It‚Äôs different for every company, and there is no ‚Äúright way‚Äù to build this out So if you‚Äôre struggling to know how to do it, take rest in knowing, you‚Äôre not Here‚Äôs what we have You ll need an "Admin" or a You ll need end users to execute on what the admin sets You ll likely need an executive sponsor for the And finally, you ll need support from product and a salesforce Admin (RevOps Growth Product): define metrics and thresholds that matter for the business End users (AEs SDRs): execute "sales plays" based on the insights that the Admin configures Executive sponsor (CRO CMO): decide who owns the project and drive towards strategic outcomes Product (supporting role): keys to product data in the warehouse or customer data platform Salesforce admin (supporting role): create the relevant custom fields in Salesforce Learning #2 - Current Solutions How are companies solving this today? There are four ways folks are putting product usage data into the hands of sales reps today: Analytics BI Tools Reverse ETL DIY Many companies have built a DIY solution, either using internal engineering resources, or by patching together multiple Le

Food Delivery: How Much are you really paying? Home Events Blog Signup More Use tab to navigate through the menu All Posts Food Tech Events Industry Recipes Food Memes Famished Los Angeles Search Abhi Chatterjee Oct 2 min read Food Delivery: How Much are you really paying? It‚Äôs probably more than you think Whether you were already lazy, or the pandemic made you, most people have increased their use of food delivery It‚Äôs easy, convenient, and after all, it is always great to have whatever food we want to be delivered to our house whilst we watch that season premiere on But, despite how good these services might be, there are multiple hidden costs that we are paying whenever we order food from these And most importantly, due to the heated competition in this market, companies are taking advantage of customers need for convenience by increasing profitability by hidden costs instead of moving towards Research made to understand these hidden costs and how much they are has shown some interesting For example, when taking the price of your meal on the app platform versus the price you would pay directly at the restaurant, cheaper apps tended to be % more expensive, and the most premium app up to % more So, on average, the convenience fee you are paying for getting your food to your doorstep is about % higher than if you went to the restaurant ‚Äî where you are already paying a convenience fee for not cooking the meal yourself nor washing the Food delivery app services will differ by the amount they charge on meal markup, service and delivery fee, and even different taxes ‚Äî it is interesting to point out that taxes vary up to %. For example, some apps will barely charge for the service but have a hefty bill for the delivery, and in other apps, it will be the other way And it isn‚Äôt only what the app charges, but how it does Some restaurants will increase their menu prices for online apps to pay the fee for being in the app (which usually goes up to %). But, some apps will list restaurants with whom they don‚Äôt have a formal The problem is that these apps can mark up the prices as high as they want, and whatever the difference from the actual restaurant price will be profit for the As expected, this can affect the name of the The main problem is not just that food delivery will be more expensive in some apps than others The biggest problem here is that apps use only price differentiation instead of user experience and innovation to increase their competitive There are plenty of ways apps could innovate to create a much better user experience, for example, ordering, for when it feels like a hamburger and poke New packaging that keeps the food in better condition whilst also being more More pictures and Diet and nutrition information would be a great way to serve its customers whilst letting them take care of their health Integration with social platforms and many other To conclude, what is important to note is that food delivery is here to stay there is no debating But we as consumers have the power to invest our money in those that are really trying to make a In the meantime, don‚Äôt disregard going to restaurants or buying local, which has no hidden costs and some might say tastes even Industry Food Delivery Food Tech Los Angeles Food Tech ‚Ä¢ Industry ‚Ä¢ Famished 5 views 0 comments Post not marked as liked Recent Posts See All Exploring LA s Vegan Playground 0 4 Post not marked as liked 4 <path d="M9.44985848 Z   Famished | LA s Newest Food Discovery App Home Events Blog Signup More Use tab to navigate through the menu Food Festivals You ve been missing out on money, data and a better experience for your Get in touch What is it? Ready mix concrete is far better than other building materials in many However, there are three overarching benefits that cover most of the perks: Durability Ready mix concrete is resistant to damage Sedation dentistry can vary from medications given in the office to relax the patient to full general anesthesia at the Children‚Äôs hospital where a child is completely asleep for As a pediatric dentist, Murray has a goal to make sure her patients are have healthy teeth that do not cause pain or infection, but also a responsibility to make sure they have positive experiences at the dentist, to allow them to grow into adults that can tolerate dental treatment without fear or Sedation with general anesthesia is utilized when a child is very young, fearful, or has many cavities in many This allows Murray to complete treatment carefully, safely and without the child having to tolerate many long At Children s Hospital Colorado, Murray works with a pediatric anesthesia team with specific training on anesthesia in If you have questions about the anesthesia process or if you child would benefit from care with general anesthesia, Murray will happily answer any questions at your child‚Äôs dental exam after meeting your family and evaluating your child‚Äôs specific What is dental anxiety? Dental anxiety is an overwhelming sense of fear or dread when faced with the prospect of dental Dental anxiety in adults can result avoiding dental care and difficulty tolerating treatments or Often this can stem from previous difficult or negative experiences at the Pediatric dentists are specialized providers that do an additional 2 years of training compared to family dentists or general dentists, learning methods to reduce dental anxiety in By modifying treatment to match children‚Äôs needs and age, Murray can make visits easier, quicker and more positive for your Sometimes kids can have anxiety even without previous dental experiences or for other For these children, Murray can explain options to treat any urgent concerns in a way that works for the family and the child, and then work with family for customized desensitization plans to help children learn to become more comfortable brushing at home and treatment in office over What happens during sedation dentistry? If your child needs to be fully sedated during dental treatments, a skilled and experienced pediatric anesthesiologist at Children‚Äôs Hospital Colorado administers the general anesthesia Often the process begins with a medication they drink to help them relax, then gases they breath through a yummy flavored mask until they are sleep, with an IV started after they are Kids often remember only drinking the medicine and then waking up to eat a popsicle after the procedure is complete! General anesthesia creates an almost immediate effect, and your child rests comfortably throughout their Once Murray completes the necessary dental work, the anesthesiologist ceases the flow of medication and the effects begin to wear Kids will be a little confused or groggy as they come out of They should take it easy for the rest of the day, and drink plenty of Often pain is managed with Tylenol or Ibuprofen for days and parents report their kids were back to playing like normal the next Learn more about your child‚Äôs treatment options during a consultation, which can be booked online or by phone Services Dental Cleaning Sedation Dentistry Early Dental Care Nitrous Oxide Emergency Dentistry Silver Diamine Fluoride Special Healthcare Needs Dentistry Iris Pediatric Dentistry | Leslie Murray, DMD √¢¬ú¬Ü Phone (appointments): √¢¬ú¬Ü Phone (general inquiries): Address: Quebec Street, Suite , Denver, CO Facebook icon Instagram icon Yelp icon Privacy Terms & Conditions Accessibility Contact Us   Guidelines | Pediatric Dentistry in Denver, CO | Iris Pediatric Dentistry Home About Our Team Guidelines Services Dental Cleaning Sedation Dentistry Early Dental Care Nitrous Oxide Emergency Dentistry Silver Diamine Fluoride Special Healthcare Needs Dentistry Testimonials Insurance Info Education Station Contact Schedule Now Text Us Guidelines Iris Pediatric Dentistry will be following local Denver, Colorado and CDC Policies and recommendations will be changing often, please refer to current page on our website or call the office for sp

Medical Cannabis in Mississippi Newsroom Opt Out List Contact Us Home ¬ª Austin‚Äôs Story Austin s Story My son, Austin, lived a happy and healthy first years of his He was happiest hanging out with his friends, being outdoors hunting, fishing, and playing Just living life and getting ready for his senior year of high But, at the age of , his world and ours were turned upside Suddenly, the health of our active teenage son was gone due to contracting Lyme Disease, which became Chronic Lyme He began having focal seizures, severe joint pain, and chronic nausea and vomiting along with several other health These debilitating medical conditions took a toll on my son‚Äôs life and Austin began losing weight rapidly because almost everything that he ate was expelled from his stomach, the focal seizures became more frequent, and the pain was so bad that he simply didn‚Äôt want to Austin no longer went out with friends but stayed home lying in During Austin‚Äôs senior year of high school, he saw over doctors and was prescribed prescription medications to take every day, many having lifelong side He lost about pounds and was too weak to hang out with his friends or to go to school My son‚Äôs body had been ravaged by these debilitating medical I recall one morning walking into his bedroom to give him his As I paused, by his bedside, I looked at him lying there and thought to myself ‚Äúmy son looks like a skeleton with a sheet over his body‚Äù. Not only was he underweight but his body was so weak by this time that I sometimes had to push him into the doctor‚Äôs offices in a wheelchair because he no longer had the strength to After trying the prescriptions and seeing over doctors in about months we were at a loss of ‚Äúwhat to do‚Äù. Our son looked like he was I grieved the loss of Austin‚Äôs health while remaining ever so grateful to my Savior, Jesus Christ, that I still had him with One day I just broke down I asked God to please take Austin‚Äôs suffering from him and give it to PLEASE, Lord, let him be healthy again I Well, God doesn‚Äôt always do what we want and when we want it BUT He did show us a path to restoring Austin‚Äôs health and quality of life through the use of medical After much prayer and careful consideration, Austin at the age of , made the decision to move to a state with a legal and regulated medical marijuana Once he moved, I stayed with him until he was well enough to be on his During this time, he became a legal resident of that state, went to see a doctor who recommended medical marijuana, and then received his medical marijuana card which made it possible for him to legally purchase medical marijuana at a highly secure and regulated dispensary to treat his seizures, severe joint pain, and chronic nausea and For Austin, medical marijuana WORKED! It subsided the horrible effects of his debilitating medical I remember thinking to myself after he had used medical marijuana, that ‚Äúthis seems like my vibrant happy son again and that was truly a Austin was able to eventually stop taking all prescriptions and gained the majority of his weight His body could keep food down and receive the nutrition that it needed, which allowed his strength to return! Austin could now ‚Äúwalk and not grow weary‚Äù. The seizures and severe pain subsided as I treasure every moment that we spend together, never taking his health for granted, because even today without medical marijuana, Austin‚Äôs seizures, pain, and vomiting share this page Facebook Twitter LinkedIn Email Print What is our Mission?
